<div><h3>GAME 230 - Rigging for Animation </h3>  <hr>This course covers the techniques involved in preparing 3D models for the animation process. Students will design efficient and intuitive rig systems using popular industry tools such as bones, joints, control objects, and constraints. Furthermore, the process of skinning and application interoperability will be explored.<br><br><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> GAME 095<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Fall & Spring<br><br></div>		</td>
